{"title":"Hot drinks on winter bike rides are a game changer","link":"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/opinion/thermal-bike-coffee-cup/","date":1612094439000,"content":"<img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/01/ETC-coffee-mug-07ec6f6.jpg?quality=45&#038;resize=620,413\" srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/01/ETC-coffee-mug-07ec6f6.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=2400,1598 2400w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/01/ETC-coffee-mug-07ec6f6.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1920,1278 1920w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/01/ETC-coffee-mug-07ec6f6.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1440,959 1440w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/01/ETC-coffee-mug-07ec6f6.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1200,799 1200w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/01/ETC-coffee-mug-07ec6f6.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=960,639 960w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/01/ETC-coffee-mug-07ec6f6.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=720,479 720w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/01/ETC-coffee-mug-07ec6f6.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=576,383 576w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/01/ETC-coffee-mug-07ec6f6.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=360,239 360w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/01/ETC-coffee-mug-07ec6f6.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=180,119 180w, \" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\" class=\"wp-image-614579 alignnone size-landscape_thumbnail\" alt=\"Coffee makers and bike mug\" title=\"ETC coffee mug\" />                                            <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">A thermal mug that fits in your bottle cage is the greatest <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/buyers-guides/best-cycling-gifts/\">gift</a> you can give yourself this winter, and I feel like an idiot for not realising this sooner. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">I’ve been riding bikes through the winter for years, supping at a near-frozen bidon of Baltic water and lamenting its glacial output, but never really addressing the problem. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">I did briefly experiment with putting hot tea in an insulated bottle of the kind <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/buyers-guides/best-cycling-water-bottles/\">normally used to keep drinks chilled in summer</a>. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">However, quaffing Lady Grey from a rubbery nozzle just felt gross, giving me a sense of unease much like the one I get when a well-meaning houseguest serves my morning Twinings in a mug I have mentally designated as coffee-only. You can’t cross the streams, okay? </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Anyway, distributor Moore Large recently sent me some ETC bike lights </span><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/first-look-friday/roval-terra-clx/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">(the ETC Watchman appears here</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">), and included in the box was a small thermal mug with a flip-up top. </span></p>\n<div class=\"image-handler__container image-handler__container--aspect\" style=\"padding-bottom: calc(100% / 1.501210653753);\">\n    <picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/01/ETC-coffee-mug-2-66919c1.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=299%2C199, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/01/ETC-coffee-mug-2-66919c1.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=599%2C399 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/01/ETC-coffee-mug-2-66919c1.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=899%2C599 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/01/ETC-coffee-mug-2-66919c1.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1199%2C799 4x\"